  "description": "## Android_Kiosk_DeviceRestriction\n\n**Type:** Device Configuration  \n**Platform:** Android Enterprise (Android device owner / dedicated device)\n\n### Description\nThis device-owner configuration targets dedicated (kiosk) Android devices and places the device into single-app kiosk mode using the app de.ozerov.fully (Fully Kiosk Browser). It explicitly blocks Bluetooth, forces the microphone to be muted, and requires Google Play Verify Apps (securityRequireVerifyApps = true). External media and USB file transfer are explicitly allowed (storageBlockExternalMedia = false, storageBlockUsbFileTransfer = false), VPN always-on lockdown is disabled, and password behavior remains at device defaults. Many kiosk customization options (status bar, system navigation, allowed Wi‑Fi SSIDs, etc.) are left not configured, so the primary enforced restrictions are the single-app lock, Bluetooth disablement, microphone mute, and app verification.",
